Hi again Sergey,

I finally found a few minutes to try Sentry with Raven on a python project.

It is possible to track exceptions from RPC methods by configuring the right logger. This also works with Raven and Sentry. Here is an example of the configuration I used:

```
LOGGING = {
    'version': 1,
    'disable_existing_loggers': False,
    'handlers': {
        'sentry': {
            'level': 'ERROR',
            'class': 'raven.handlers.logging.SentryHandler',
            'dsn': "https://xxx:zzz@sentry.io/123456789",
        },
    },
    'loggers': {
        'modernrpc': {
            'handlers': ['sentry'],
            'level': 'INFO',
            'propagate': True,
        },
    }
}
```

With this very basic configuration, I can track and report errors to Sentry, even with current version of django-modern-rpc (0.9.0). In addition, I checked with current development version (not released yet) and the new ``settings.MODERNRPC_LOG_EXCEPTION``. In this case, Sentry can access to the full exception stacktrace which is more useful.

I close this issue for now, since you have a sample config to redirect modernrpc exceptions to sentry. I will open another ticket to improve the documentation and explain how error management can be configured.

Best regards !

