I was actually right now writing about this... there should be a clean interface to register stuff to the menu hierarchy, because currently there isn't... with the dynamic example you are not registering so the API functions to traverse doesn't work with it.

Another example is, say you have an action with a variable path and you have a concrete action for a specific path which happens to be inside of that hierarchy you end up with not initialized menu entries, because the dynamic generator hasn't been called, and your menu hierarchy is not established. In that case you have to add .register_menu calls to the variable path action view to register the parents of the concrete one. Rough example:
```python
  @bp.route('/<path:path>')
  @menu.register_menu(... dynamic_list_constructor=...)
  def page(path):
      pass

  @bp.route('/a/b/c')
  @menu.register_menu(...)
  def c():
      pass
```
In this case you have to add via decorators the call to register menu so that the parents for c are registered:
```python
  @bp.route('/<path:path>')
  @menu.register_menu(... dynamic_list_constructor=...)
  @menu.register_menu(...)
  @menu.register_menu(...)
  def page(path):
      pass
```
A scenario I see you may want to register your hierarchy beforehand is with the use of Flask-Flatpages...

In my case I ended up writing my own simple solution.

