@mcg1969 
> But just to be clear, if you're suggesting that the channel logic should go into VersionOrder I'd say no. I think this needs to sit between VersionOrder and MatchSpec somehow.

This is what I mean: I suggest to change the `VersionOrder` constructor into `__init__(self, version, priority=0)`, where `priority` is a numerical priority that conda derives from the `channel_priority` spec (higher numbers mean higher priority). The priority can simply be prepended to the parsed `self.version` at the end of the constructor. Thus, higher priority channels will be treated like higher version numbers, without any additional programming. Isn't this convenient? But if you choose to implement it differently, this is fine with me.

